text: I'm sorry, but horror films *REALLY* hold back. I mean, what happened to super, ultra, horrendously scary visuals? I feel like nowadays horror movies are just trying to give you a damn heart attack with the all the jump scares. Some guy had a seizure during a screening of "Annabelle" probably because of a jump scare while i was watching.  I mean, I just want something that is so shockingly frightening that you can't look at it - *I'M NOT TALKING ABOUT VIOLENCE AND GORE*. Sound and visuals.  "Mama" the first half of the movie is scary, but then they had jumpscares and all of the crap cgi. "Evil Dead" was awesome, and I'm not talking about the violence and gore.

text: Maybe Elise is forced to make an unholy alliance with other demonic forces in the Further?  I know it's a stretch, but when the black and sludgy demon clearly has a hold on the girl's soul to the point that her limbs and eyes have shriveled away, maybe Elise is forced to seek the help of other demonic entities, at a terrible price that she is willing to ignore in the moment in order to save the girl--like showing them that stealing a child's soul is the secret to walking freely among the living and letting them fight to a standstill while she rescues the girl?  Then red face and Parker become a part of Elise's history because they now have a craving for human life and they know that she double-crossed them?  Maybe she even goes so far as to lie out of desperation, promising them the girl or promising a substitute soul?  No matter what, I think it would be cool if the entities we are familiar with were laced with her rescue mission in such a way that they are beneficial to the rescue of this girl, but also in a way that sets them up as future antagonists that are not very fond of Elise.
